Here's a complete example:

**Product.cs**
```csharp
public class Product
{
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public decimal Price { get; set; }
}
```

**MainPage.xaml**
```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:models="clr-namespace:YourApp.Models"
             x:Class="YourApp.MainPage">

    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Products}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Product">
                <HorizontalStackLayout Padding="12" Spacing="8">
                    <Label Text="{Binding Name}"
                           FontSize="16"
                           VerticalOptions="Center" />
                    <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='{0:C}'}"
                           FontSize="14"
                           TextColor="Gray"
                           VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </HorizontalStackLayout>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
    </CollectionView>

</ContentPage>
```

**MainPage.xaml.cs**
```csharp
using System.Collections.ObjectModel;

public partial class MainPage : ContentPage
{
    public ObservableCollection<Product> Products { get; } = new()
    {
        new Product { Name = "Widget", Price = 9.99m },
        new Product { Name = "Gadget", Price = 24.95m },
        new Product { Name = "Doohickey", Price = 4.50m }
    };

    public MainPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = this;
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`x:DataType="models:Product"`** on the `DataTemplate` enables compiled bindings — catches binding errors at build time and improves performance.
- **`ObservableCollection<T>`** ensures the UI updates automatically when items are added/removed.
- The default `ItemsLayout` is `VerticalList`, so no extra configuration is needed for vertical scrolling.
- Never use `ViewCell` — use a layout like `HorizontalStackLayout` directly as the template root.
